<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-03-28T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-03-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="811" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d811">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 741.8215/40.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">American Ambassador to
                                    Great Britain</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-03-28">
                                    <hi rend="italic">March 28, 1912</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>The substance of your telegram of the 27th instant<note n="1" xml:id="d811fn1">Not printed.</note> has been cabled to the American
                            Minister at Monrovia and he has been instructed to urge upon the
                            Government of Liberia the absolute necessity of an immediate compliance
                            with the demands of the British Government. Advise the Foreign Office of
                            the action of this Government, and, in view of the present status of the
                            loan negotiations, intimate our hope that the British Government will
                            feel inclined to the utmost patience to bring about a satisfactory
                            solution of the difficulty.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>